			<p class="tucked"><br /><strong>Skype. On your phone. For reals.</strong><br />In early 2010, Skype introduced its revolutionary mobile app which for the first time ever allowed its users to place Skype calls from their mobile phones. To get Skype's huge user base excited about it, we armed five outdoor artists scattered around the globe with Skype-enabled phones, who would transform user's messages into bespoke, shareable video content. 
			</p>

			<p class="tucked"><strong>Operator, make me an ice sculpture</strong><br />Skype users from across the world called the artists directly from the Skype Outside homepage to leave messages they wanted to give someone, and each artists turned the best ones into performances. Messages were transformed into woodcarvings, snow murals, circus acts and sculptures, and it was all filmed and put online. 
			</p>
			
			<p class="tucked"><strong>Passing on the message</strong><br />Each video message was sent back to its sender and added to the artist's YouTube channel for everyone to enjoy. We soon had a wealth of content, wrapping the product story and human story into one. People not only understood the message, they also interacted with the product and Skype got to remind the world that it is a human brand.
			</p>
						
